I got Korean red sauce on top because I didn't want sauces with mayo, and everything was delicious and fresh. I actually really enjoyed it, but the chicken was a tad dry. I'm really tempted to give this 4 stars because of the freshness of all the ingredients and the chewiness of the noodles, but I can't because of the dryness of the chicken. There's free miso soup as well but it was really salty; I wasn't a fan of that. At $9.89 post-tax, the bowl was fairly priced for the amount of food given, and the interior of the place was spacious, clean, and pleasant.

When Bibibop opened in Chinatown in July 2017, I was unimpressed by the lack of Korean toppings - black bean, corn, potato toppings, shreded cheese, and had to pay extra for Kimichi...what?! Fully deserving 2 stars. Since then Bibibop has really upped their game with slithery Jap Chae Noodles, FREE Kimichi, and better ingredients. They even have wraps too!  Bibibop is more of a Poke bowl spot than traditional Bibimibap, you won't find any stone bowls or fresh fried eggs here!  I got a custom Veggie bowl with 1/2 Salad, 1/2 Jap Chae Noodles, and loaded with veggies - Cabbage, Cucumber, Corn, Potato, Carros, Tofu, Kimichi, and topped with Yum Yum (Sriracha Mayo) and Teriyaki. The heaping bowl was DELISH - very filling and satisfying! The sweet potato Jap Chae Noodles were tasty and fully delivered on absorbing all the spices and flavor from the other ingredients. I delightfully watched a fresh batch being cooked in a Wok, the food is fresh!  Lunch time rush - the lines go by quickly. There were a dozen people in front of me, within 15 minutes, I was swiftly in and out!  Don't miss the self-serve sauce station on the side (behind the beverage station), so plenty of sauces to go around!  Great spot for lunch - looking forward to a heaping bowl of those glass noodles!
